  "source": [
    "## Feature Grouping for Consumer Behavior Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "To support an AI-powered consumer behavior insight agent, features are grouped into the following categories:\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1. Behavioral Signals (How customers behave)\n",
    "- Time_Spent_on_Product_Research(hours)\n",
    "- Time_to_Decision\n",
    "- Engagement_with_Ads\n",
    "- Social_Media_Influence\n",
    "- Discount_Sensitivity\n",
    "- Shipping_Preference\n",
    "- Return_Rate\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2. Intent & Mindset Signals (Why customers buy)\n",
    "- Purchase_Intent (Planned, Impulsive, Need-based, Wants-based)\n",
    "- Discount_Used\n",
    "- Brand_Loyalty\n",
    "- Customer_Loyalty_Program_Member\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3. Transaction & Context (What customers do)\n",
    "- Purchase_Category\n",
    "- Purchase_Amount\n",
    "- Frequency_of_Purchase\n",
    "- Purchase_Channel\n",
    "- Device_Used_for_Shopping\n",
    "- Payment_Method\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4. Outcomes & Satisfaction (What happens after)\n",
    "- Customer_Satisfaction\n",
    "- Product_Rating\n",
    "- Return_Rate\n",
    "\n",
    "These groupings will drive segmentation, intent modeling, and insight generation in the Shoplytics agent.\n"
  ]
}

